## 4. Identification Strategy

OLS-with-controls: no remaining confounders after controls
Fixed effects: time-invariant omitted factors are removed
DiD: parallel trends in the absence of treatment
RDD: local random assignment around the cutoff
IV: exclusion restriction / instrument affects outcome only through treatment

